McKay, Respondent, v. Brewster, Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 12, 1890.) Appeal from judgment of the city court.

Argued before Labremore, C. J., and Bookstaver, J.

Charles E. Le Barbiere, for appellant. Thomas D. Rambaut, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the judgment be affirmed, with costs.
